View loaded definitions

 

The application administrator is able to view the list of all loaded model definitions in the system.

  • In the Administration menu/ section "Import/ export models" (1) there is a list of all loaded Definitions (2).
    • For each definition is displayed information for (3): Identifier, Type - from the CL, Abstract, File name, Modified on - the date of loading it in the system, Modified by - the user who uploaded/changed it.
    • The definitions can be filtered by text (4). We can filter by all columns and all tables.

 

In "Import/ export models" (1) there is a list of all loaded Templates (5). The templates are presented with a header (7) which is a link to open the Template landing page.

  • For each template is display information for (6): Title, Template purpose, Primary template, Object type for the template, Мodified by - the user who uploaded/changed it, Мodified on - the date of loading it in the system.
  • The templates can be filtered by text (4). We can filter by all columns and all tables.

 

Download definitions (models)

 

The administrator is able to download one or more of the definitions (models) uploaded in SEP.

  • In the Administration menu/ section "Manage models" (1) there is Download action.
  • The user could select one or more of the definitions (2-3) and select the action Download (4).
    • There is Select all in the list with definitions, and the user could select all of the listed definitions.
  • The action Download is active only if one or more definitions are selected.

Notes:

- Currently only files for model definitions and templates will be available for download.

- When the action Download is selected then all of the selected definitions are downloaded in a zip file.
